cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.SE 

This paper is about improving the efficiency of NeuroEvolution, which is a subfield of machine learning focused on optimizing artificial neural networks using evolutionary algorithms. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of surrogate model-based optimization, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The benchmark task used in the study involves reinforcement learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the extension of cartesian genetic programming, which is a technique used in software engineering, falling under the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
